gomodel:SYNGO_2930  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Cellular and subcellular localization of ANO1 in the retina\"\n- \"ANO1 puncta in the OPL, where photoreceptor terminals synapse onto bipolar and horizontal cell dendrites, showed immunoreactivities for synaptophysin and vesicular glutamate transporter 1 (VGLUT1), which are markers of photoreceptor terminals (Figs. 2A and B)\"\n\nFig.4: \"Presynaptic localization of ANO1 in the retina\"\n- \"In the OPL, cone pedicles and rod spherules were labeled for ANO1, whereas invaginating ON-bipolar and horizontal cell dendrites, which are postsynaptic elements located at the ribbon synapse of photoreceptor terminals, and OFF-bipolar cell dendrites, which make basal junctions with cone pedicles, were unlabeled (Figs. 4A and B).\"\n\nNotes:\n- I have refrained from making a BP annotation since the data lack synaptic context.\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Three-month-old male C57BL/6 mice (Orient Bio, Seongnam, Korea) were used in this study. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2930" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

